\fs26 III. FUTURE WORK
\fs24 \

\fs26 We plan to continue developing and refining the methods through which Melody Matcher makes its determinations. Eventually, we plan to use this as an underlying framework for an interactive virtual environment where your surroundings are affected and created via musical and lyrical input. This should be completed in March 2012, with incremental updates discussed on www.melodymatcher.com.
\fs24 \

\fs26 IV. CONCLUSION
\fs24 \

\fs26 In this paper, we have discussed at a high level parts of the music-lingustic approach that Melody Matcher takes to measure the intelligibility of lyrics. We covered some of the major reasons that lyrics get misheard, along with a few examples. Melody Matcher\'92s specific implementation details, while fully specified elsewhere, were outside the scope of this abstract, and we hope to cover them in a later paper.
